    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn19.15:1.1",
          "pli": "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ itthiṃ uppakkaṃ okiliniṃ okiriniṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ. ",
          "en": "“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a scorched woman, sooty and sweaty, flying through the air, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn19.15:1.2",
          "pli": "Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe … ",
          "en": "as she screamed in pain. …” … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn19.15:1.3",
          "pli": "esā, bhikkhave, itthī kaliṅgassa rañño aggamahesī ahosi. ",
          "en": "“That woman used to be the king of Kaliṅga’s chief queen. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn19.15:1.4",
          "pli": "Sā issāpakatā sapattiṃ aṅgārakaṭāhena okiri … pe …. ",
          "en": "She was of jealous nature, and poured a brazier of hot coals over her co-wife. …” … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn19.15:1.5",
          "pli": "Pañcamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
